  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRunning tests locally on MacOs fails with:\r\n\r\n`du: invalid option -- b`\r\n\r\nThis is due to the line:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst res = execSync(`du -bs ${dbLocation}`, {encoding: \"utf8\"});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat can be found in this test [here](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/daf2f2821364b4d5ea8b9d5bfa2b8e59f951eba1/packages/db/test/unit/controller/level.test.ts#L140)\r\n\r\nReason this fails is that, apparently the `-b` is not in the `du` spec and not supported on MacOs. This means this will also fail on windows by the way.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nThe tests should run fine on MacOs (also windows) and should not be dependent on OS. ",
